{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"## WS7 plan-review triage (PASS, 16 advisories) — 2026-07-01\n\nExecuting via the user-chosen PROVE-THEN-LOCK sequence: write CONTRIBUTING.md → dogfood it\nthrough Gerrit (proves LLM-Review votes + replication reaches GitHub main) → checkpoint → lock.\n\nAddressed now:\n- adv 3,4 (no pre-flight that the LLM-Review bot is up before locking): HANDLED by prove-then-lock\n  — the dogfood submit proves the bot votes + replication works BEFORE the lock is applied.\n- adv 11 (PR-triggered CI dies post-cutover): NOT a functional break — test/optionality/eval also\n  trigger on `push: branches:[\"**\"]`, so CI still runs when Gerrit replicates to main. The\n  `pull_request:` trigger becomes vestigial (optional cleanup, noted).\n- adv 8,10,14 (doc dangling refs + missing-Change-Id-hook path): authoring CONTRIBUTING.md fresh —\n  no dangling 'S7 runbook' ref; will cover the missing-hook non-happy path explicitly.\n- adv 13 (file_impact): set.\n\nSurfacing at the PRE-LOCK checkpoint (policy calls for the user):\n- adv 1 (CRITICAL): the tag-lock ruleset would reject human `v*` tag pushes → breaks\n  .github/workflows/release.yml (PyPI publish on `push: tags`). Options: lock main only (leave tags\n  unlocked), or lock tags + push release tags via the deploy key / a CI bypass. Decide before applying.\n- adv 16: check/drain open PRs against main before locking. Current open PRs: (see command output).\n- adv 7: TF `check` only WARNs (won't abort if deploy key absent) → I'll pre-verify the\n  rebar-gerrit-replication key is present (confirmed id 155914477) and use an explicit fail-closed\n  pre-check at apply, or convert to a lifecycle precondition.\n\nDeferred as follow-up observability tickets (good hygiene, not blocking the cutover):\n- adv 2,9,15 (Terraform drift reconciliation + proving commands), adv 5 (replication-health +\n  ruleset-drift alerts), adv 6 (recurring ruleset-active check). Will create discovered_from tickets."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782935582340185001,"uuid":"528e1e61-0a97-4662-844c-a1862a0d7f1f"}